                            <comment id="17743987" author="dcapwell" created="Mon, 17 Jul 2023 21:53:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is what I think is happening so far&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
topologies = node.topology().withUnsyncedEpochs(route, txnId.epoch() == 4, executeAt.epoch() == 5);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here, epoch 4 knows about the keyspace, but epoch 5 does not; aka we are running the txn in a topology that would have rejected it in the first place...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17743999" author="dcapwell" created="Mon, 17 Jul 2023 23:04:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;spoke with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=benedict&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;benedict&quot;&gt;benedict&lt;/a&gt; and we agree on a solution&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) in pre-accept we know that the execution id&apos;s epoch != txn epoch, so we can check that the new topology &quot;supports&quot; the txn; else we reject&lt;br/&gt;
2) we need to invalidate the txn&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17759749" author="dcapwell" created="Mon, 28 Aug 2023 22:18:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is turning out more complex than originally planned, mostly due to the semantics of exclusive sync points... here is one problem found&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;T0: range movement so node1 now has a new range (that already existed)&lt;br/&gt;
T1: drop range (drop keyspace/ table)&lt;br/&gt;
T2: node1&apos;s bootstrap of the new range is failing as we have to run in the latest epoch, which doesn&apos;t know the range!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Spoke with Benedict and we agreed to punt this work for now in favor of other work, and to get back to this in ~3 weeks...  but the starting work for add keyspace support (mostly bug fixes) could go in now; so will create a new JIRA for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17876779" author="dcapwell" created="Mon, 26 Aug 2024 16:29:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;picking this back up.  The current plan is to do&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) change TCM to make drop table with accord enabled to be a 3 phased things&lt;br/&gt;
2) new phase is: mark dropping, await for accord to complete, drop&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17884689" author="dcapwell" created="Wed, 25 Sep 2024 17:36:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;renamed ticket to reflect that Accord is no longer Keyspace based but Table based...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17885052" author="beobal" created="Thu, 26 Sep 2024 14:48:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve reworked the TCM elements of this a bit and pushed an updated version to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/beobal/cassandra/tree/samt/CASSANDRA-18675&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/beobal/cassandra/tree/samt/CASSANDRA-18675&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I haven&apos;t modified any tests (except for where names have been changed) and are all still passing (I see a handful of timeouts in CI, but those pass locally).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m just working on adding operator controls to resume a drop table sequence should the coordinator fail midway, and then I&apos;ll take a better look at the CI timeouts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17885061" author="beobal" created="Thu, 26 Sep 2024 15:25:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added a rather rudimentary nodetool command to resume a failed table drop. It would be nice to add a vtable interface to expose more information about in-flight operations, but that probably deserves its own JIRA.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17885460" author="beobal" created="Fri, 27 Sep 2024 19:20:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;PR LGTM, so +1 assuming CI is good&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
